{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775851066314,"sessionID":"ses_287086c38ffeMTxMJSl10GYi0l","part":{"id":"prt_d78f80e5a001W7gdzZclpIdAw3","messageID":"msg_d78f7fe22001yKxEdIfcbzsdcF","sessionID":"ses_287086c38ffeMTxMJSl10GYi0l","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_5b77e0d6e0334209b7476aea","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/proposal.md","content":"# AR-011: Router JWT Authentication & Issuance\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis proposal implements JWT (JSON Web Token) authentication for the `pkg/router` module in the AgentCube project. The goal is to:\n\n1. **Secure router endpoints** - Require valid JWT tokens for accessing backend services through the router\n2. **Enable stateless authentication** - Use JWT's self-contained nature to avoid server-side session lookups for token validation\n3. **Support token issuance** - Provide endpoints for issuing JWT tokens upon successful authentication\n4. **Integrate with existing session management** - Complement the existing session middleware with JWT-based authentication\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** `pkg/router`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M\n\nThis AR covers:\n\n- **In scope:**\n  - JWT validation middleware for router HTTP handlers\n  - JWT issuance endpoint for token generation\n  - Configuration for JWT secrets and token expiration\n  - Integration with existing session management\n  - Unit tests for JWT validation and issuance\n\n- **Out of scope:**\n  - User authentication logic (username/password validation)\n  - OAuth2/OIDC integration\n  - Token refresh mechanisms\n  - RBAC/authorization policies (future AR)\n\n## Current State Analysis\n\n### Existing Authentication Mechanisms\n\nThe current router implementation has session-based authentication:\n\n1. **Session Middleware** (`middleware/session_middleware.go`):\n   - Extracts session ID from cookies or headers\n   - Validates session against session store (memory/Redis)\n   - Attaches session to request context\n   - `RequireSession` middleware enforces authentication\n\n2. **Session Types** (`session/types.go`):\n   - `Session` struct with ID, namespace, kind, backend info\n   - Session state management (Active, Idle, Expired, Terminated)\n   - Configurable expiration and idle timeouts\n\n3. **Session Manager** (`session/manager.go`):\n   - CRUD operations for sessions\n   - Session cleanup and expiration handling\n\n### Issues Identified\n\n1. **Stateful authentication** - Every request requires a session store lookup\n2. **No token-based auth** - External clients cannot easily authenticate without session cookies\n3. **Limited scalability** - Session store becomes a bottleneck for distributed deployments\n4. **No standard protocol** - Proprietary session mechanism vs. industry-standard JWT\n\n### Kubernetes Client-Go Context\n\nPer `deployment/client-go.md`, the generated client-go library provides:\n- Typed clients for `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` resources\n- Informers for watching resource changes\n- Listers for efficient caching\n\n**Note:** JWT authentication in the router is orthogonal to Kubernetes RBAC. The router operates at the HTTP layer, while Kubernetes RBAC controls access to the API server.\n\n## Proposed Changes\n\n### 1. JWT Configuration\n\nAdd JWT configuration to `config.go`:\n\n```go\ntype JWTConfig struct {\n    // Enabled enables JWT authentication\n    Enabled bool `json:\"enabled\"`\n    \n    // Secret is the JWT signing secret (HMAC) or path to private key (RSA/ECDSA)\n    Secret string `json:\"secret\"`\n    \n    // SecretPath is the path to the JWT secret file\n    SecretPath string `json:\"secretPath\"`\n    \n    // Algorithm is the signing algorithm (HS256, RS256, ES256)\n    Algorithm string `json:\"algorithm\"`\n    \n    // TokenExpiration is the JWT token expiration duration\n    TokenExpiration time.Duration `json:\"tokenExpiration\"`\n    \n    // Issuer is the JWT issuer claim\n    Issuer string `json:\"issuer\"`\n    \n    // Audience is the expected audience claim\n    Audience string `json:\"audience\"`\n}\n\ntype RouterConfig struct {\n    // ... existing fields ...\n    JWT JWTConfig `json:\"jwt\"`\n}\n```\n\n### 2. JWT Claims Structure\n\nDefine custom claims for AgentCube-specific data:\n\n```go\ntype JWTClaims struct {\n    jwt.RegisteredClaims\n    \n    // UserID is the authenticated user's identifier\n    UserID string `json:\"userId\"`\n    \n    // Namespace is the allowed Kubernetes namespace (optional)\n    Namespace string `json:\"namespace,omitempty\"`\n    \n    // Roles is the list of assigned roles (for future RBAC)\n    Roles []string `json:\"roles,omitempty\"`\n    \n    // SessionID links to an existing session (optional)\n    SessionID string `json:\"sessionId,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n### 3. JWT Middleware\n\nCreate `middleware/jwt_middleware.go`:\n\n```go\ntype JWTMiddleware struct {\n    config *JWTConfig\n    key    interface{} // Signing key\n}\n\nfunc (m *JWTMiddleware) Validate(next http.Handler) http.Handler {\n    return http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n        token, err := m.extractToken(r)\n        if err != nil {\n            m.writeError(w, \"missing token\", http.StatusUnauthorized)\n            return\n        }\n        \n        claims, err := m.validateToken(token)\n        if err != nil {\n            m.writeError(w, \"invalid token\", http.StatusUnauthorized)\n            return\n        }\n        \n        ctx := context.WithValue(r.Context(), JWTClaimsContextKey, claims)\n        r = r.WithContext(ctx)\n        next.ServeHTTP(w, r)\n    })\n}\n```\n\n### 4. JWT Issuance Endpoint\n\nAdd token issuance handler in `handler.go`:\n\n```go\nfunc (h *Handler) IssueToken(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n    // Extract credentials from request\n    creds, err := h.extractCredentials(r)\n    if err != nil {\n        h.writeError(w, \"invalid credentials\", http.StatusUnauthorized)\n        return\n    }\n    \n    // Validate credentials (delegate to auth provider)\n    user, err := h.authProvider.Authenticate(r.Context(), creds)\n    if err != nil {\n        h.writeError(w, \"authentication failed\", http.StatusUnauthorized)\n        return\n    }\n    \n    // Generate JWT\n    token, err := h.jwtSigner.Sign(user)\n    if err != nil {\n        h.writeError(w, \"token generation failed\", http.StatusInternalServerError)\n        return\n    }\n    \n    // Return token\n    json.NewEncoder(w).Encode(TokenResponse{\n        Token:     token,\n        ExpiresIn: h.config.JWT.TokenExpiration.Seconds(),\n    })\n}\n```\n\n### 5. Router Integration\n\nUpdate `router.go` to optionally enable JWT middleware:\n\n```go\nfunc (r *Router) Start(ctx context.Context) error {\n    var handler http.Handler = r.handler\n    \n    if r.config.JWT.Enabled {\n        jwtMiddleware := middleware.NewJWTMiddleware(&r.config.JWT)\n        handler = jwtMiddleware.Validate(handler)\n    }\n    \n    server := &http.Server{\n        Addr:         r.config.ListenAddr,\n        Handler:      handler,\n        ReadTimeout:  r.config.ReadTimeout,\n        WriteTimeout: r.config.WriteTimeout,\n        IdleTimeout:  r.config.IdleTimeout,\n    }\n    \n    // ... rest of startup logic ...\n}\n```\n\n### 6. Token Issuance Route\n\nAdd dedicated route for token issuance (bypasses JWT validation):\n\n```go\nfunc (h *Handler) ServeHTTP(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n    // Token issuance endpoint (no auth required)\n    if r.Method == http.MethodPost && r.URL.Path == \"/api/v1/auth/token\" {\n        h.IssueToken(w, r)\n        return\n    }\n    \n    // All other routes require JWT\n    route, err := h.resolver.Resolve(r)\n    if err != nil {\n        h.writeError(w, err, http.StatusNotFound)\n        return\n    }\n    \n    if err := h.ProxyRequest(w, r, route); err != nil {\n        h.writeError(w, err, http.StatusBadGateway)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Files to Create\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `pkg/router/middleware/jwt_middleware.go` | JWT validation middleware |\n| `pkg/router/middleware/jwt_middleware_test.go` | Middleware unit tests |\n| `pkg/router/jwt_signer.go` | JWT signing utilities |\n| `pkg/router/jwt_signer_test.go` | Signer unit tests |\n\n### Files to Modify\n\n| File | Changes | Impact |\n|------|---------|--------|\n| `pkg/router/config.go` | Add `JWTConfig` struct | Low - backward compatible |\n| `pkg/router/router.go` | Integrate JWT middleware | Medium - affects request flow |\n| `pkg/router/handler.go` | Add token issuance endpoint | Medium - new route |\n| `pkg/router/types.go` | Add JWT claims context key | Low - additive |\n\n### Dependencies\n\nAdd to `go.mod`:\n- `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` - JWT parsing and signing\n- Optionally: `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5/request` - Token extraction helpers\n\n### Backward Compatibility\n\n- JWT authentication is **disabled by default** (`JWTConfig.Enabled = false`)\n- Existing session-based auth continues to work\n- Can run both session and JWT middleware in parallel\n\n### Testing Impact\n\n- Unit tests for JWT signing and validation\n- Integration tests for token issuance endpoint\n- E2E tests for authenticated routing\n- Existing tests unaffected (JWT disabled by default)\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Kubernetes ServiceAccount Tokens\n\nUse Kubernetes ServiceAccount tokens directly.\n\n**Pros:**\n- No additional token management\n- Integrates with Kubernetes RBAC\n- Standard for in-cluster communication\n\n**Cons:**\n- Tied to Kubernetes cluster\n- Requires API server access for validation\n- Overkill for simple router auth\n- Limited custom claims\n\n**Decision:** Defer for future Kubernetes-native integration. JWT provides more flexibility.\n\n### Alternative 2: mTLS (Mutual TLS)\n\nRequire client certificates for authentication.\n\n**Pros:**\n- Strong authentication\n- No token management\n- Encrypted by default\n\n**Cons:**\n- Complex certificate management\n- Poor UX for external clients\n- Harder to debug\n- No fine-grained claims\n\n**Decision:** Too complex for current requirements. Consider for zero-trust deployments.\n\n### Alternative 3: Opaque Bearer Tokens\n\nUse random opaque tokens with server-side storage.\n\n**Pros:**\n- Simple implementation\n- Easy to revoke\n- No JWT complexity\n\n**Cons:**\n- Requires token store lookup on every request\n- Scalability bottleneck\n- More infrastructure to maintain\n\n**Decision:** JWT's stateless validation is preferable for router performance.\n\n### Alternative 4: OAuth2/OIDC\n\nIntegrate with full OAuth2/OIDC provider.\n\n**Pros:**\n- Industry standard\n- Rich ecosystem\n- Built-in user management\n\n**Cons:**\n- Significant implementation complexity\n- Requires OAuth2 server\n- Overkill for service-to-service auth\n\n**Decision:** Defer until user authentication requirements mature.\n\n## Implementation Checklist\n\n- [ ] Add `JWTConfig` to `pkg/router/config.go`\n- [ ] Create `pkg/router/middleware/jwt_middleware.go`\n- [ ] Create `pkg/router/jwt_signer.go`\n- [ ] Add token issuance endpoint to `pkg/router/handler.go`\n- [ ] Update `pkg/router/router.go` to integrate JWT middleware\n- [ ] Write unit tests for JWT validation\n- [ ] Write integration tests for token issuance\n- [ ] Update documentation in `deployment/`\n- [ ] Add example JWT configuration to manifests\n\n## Future Considerations\n\n1. **Token Refresh** - Implement refresh token mechanism for long-lived sessions\n2. **RBAC Integration** - Use JWT `roles` claim for authorization decisions\n3. **JWKS Support** - Fetch signing keys from JWKS endpoint for multi-tenant setups\n4. **Token Revocation** - Maintain token blacklist for revocation (Redis-backed)\n5. **OAuth2/OIDC** - Integrate with external identity providers\n6. **ServiceAccount Integration** - Accept Kubernetes ServiceAccount tokens\n7. **Audit Logging** - Log JWT claims for audit trails\n\n## References\n\n- [RFC 7519 - JSON Web Token (JWT)](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7519)\n- [github.com/golang-jwt/jwt](https://github.com/golang-jwt/jwt)\n- [Kubernetes Authentication](https://kubernetes.io/docs/reference/access-authn-authz/authentication/)\n- Existing session implementation: `pkg/router/session/`\n- Session middleware: `pkg/router/middleware/session_middleware.go`\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/agentruntime_reconciler.go\">\nERROR [166:12] undefined: json\n</diagnostics>","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/router/config.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/router/router.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":93,"character":39},"end":{"line":93,"character":50}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#any"},"source":"any","message":"interface{} can be replaced by any"},{"range":{"start":{"line":125,"character":53},"end":{"line":125,"character":64}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#any"},"source":"any","message":"interface{} can be replaced by any"},{"range":{"start":{"line":129,"character":42},"end":{"line":129,"character":53}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#any"},"source":"any","message":"interface{} can be replaced by any"},{"range":{"start":{"line":149,"character":42},"end":{"line":149,"character":53}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/go